Angle Calculation and Moire Lattice Construction¶

The details about angle calculation can be found here. In this section, we will see how to construct the commensurate moiré lattice based on the commensurate angles.

In [ ]:
Copied! 
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

from moirepy import BilayerMoireLattice, TriangularLayer, SquareLayer, KagomeLayer, HexagonalLayer
import numpy as np import matplotlib.pyplot as plt from moirepy import BilayerMoireLattice, TriangularLayer, SquareLayer, KagomeLayer, HexagonalLayer

Triangular Moire Lattice¶

Copied! 
## Make the lattice (Lattice type, a(ll1), b(ll2), m(ul1), n(ul2), x_no, y_no)---  
## don't put fractional values for x_no and y_no, which are number of moire unit cells
lattice_tri = BilayerMoireLattice(TriangularLayer, 3, 4, 4, 3, 1, 1) 
##upper layer is not translated and pbc condition true by default.----
## Make the lattice (Lattice type, a(ll1), b(ll2), m(ul1), n(ul2), x_no, y_no)--- ## don't put fractional values for x_no and y_no, which are number of moire unit cells lattice_tri = BilayerMoireLattice(TriangularLayer, 3, 4, 4, 3, 1, 1) ##upper layer is not translated and pbc condition true by default.----
twist angle = 0.1646 rad (9.4300 deg)
37 points in lower lattice
37 points in upper lattice

Please refer to the calculator to find your suitable values for (a), (b), (m), and (n).

lattice_sqr = BilayerMoireLattice(SquareLayer, 3, 4, 4, 3, 2, 2)
## We increase the number of moire unit cells along moire lattice vectors to 2,2
lattice_sqr = BilayerMoireLattice(SquareLayer, 3, 4, 4, 3, 2, 2) ## We increase the number of moire unit cells along moire lattice vectors to 2,2
twist angle = 0.2838 rad (16.2602 deg)

# Suupose we want to access the moire lattice vectors and unit cell area of the square lattice
mlv1 = np.array(lattice_sqr.mlv1)  # first moire lattice vector
mlv2 = np.array(lattice_sqr.mlv2)  # second moire lattice vector
print("First moire lattice vector:", mlv1)
print("Second moire lattice vector:", mlv2)
print("Moire lattice area:", np.linalg.norm(np.cross(mlv1, mlv2)))
# Suupose we want to access the moire lattice vectors and unit cell area of the square lattice mlv1 = np.array(lattice_sqr.mlv1) # first moire lattice vector mlv2 = np.array(lattice_sqr.mlv2) # second moire lattice vector print("First moire lattice vector:", mlv1) print("Second moire lattice vector:", mlv2) print("Moire lattice area:", np.linalg.norm(np.cross(mlv1, mlv2)))
